    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A colorless, solid, water soluble carbonate perhydrate, sodium percarbonate is a highly concentrated source of anhydrous hydrogen peroxide used as a bleaching agent in many applications including paper and textile conservation.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
